## Agent Management Quick Reference

- List board agents:
  `curl -fsS "$BASE_URL/api/v1/agent/agents?board_id=$BOARD_ID" -H "X-Agent-Token: $AUTH_TOKEN"`
- Get board snapshot:
  `curl -fsS "$BASE_URL/api/v1/agent/boards/$BOARD_ID/snapshot" -H "X-Agent-Token: $AUTH_TOKEN"`
- Create persistent board specialist:
  `curl -fsS -X POST "$BASE_URL/api/v1/agent/agents" -H "X-Agent-Token: $AUTH_TOKEN" -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"name":"Athena"}'`
- Update an existing board specialist:
  `curl -fsS -X PATCH "$BASE_URL/api/v1/agent/boards/$BOARD_ID/agents/<agent_id>" -H "X-Agent-Token: $AUTH_TOKEN" -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"name":"Hermes","identity_profile":{"role":"Operations Specialist"}}'`
- Update recurring SOUL guidance:
  `curl -fsS -X PUT "$BASE_URL/api/v1/agent/boards/$BOARD_ID/agents/<agent_id>/soul" -H "X-Agent-Token: $AUTH_TOKEN" -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"content":"..."}'`
- Delete obsolete non-lead board agent:
  `curl -fsS -X DELETE "$BASE_URL/api/v1/agent/boards/$BOARD_ID/agents/<agent_id>" -H "X-Agent-Token: $AUTH_TOKEN"`

## Capacity Rule

- `max_agents` excludes the lead.
- Count only non-lead board agents against the cap.
- If snapshot shows the lead plus 2 workers and `max_agents=3`, one worker slot remains available.
- Do not use `agents_list` or `sessions_spawn` to decide whether a persistent board agent can be created.
- Do not use org-admin `PATCH /api/v1/agents/<agent_id>` with `X-Agent-Token` for board-agent updates; that route expects org-admin auth and will return `401`.

## Board Lead Route Templates

- Task list route: `/api/v1/agent/boards/{board_id}/tasks`
- Task detail route: `/api/v1/agent/boards/{board_id}/tasks/{task_id}`
- Board snapshot route: `/api/v1/agent/boards/{board_id}/snapshot`
- Board agents route: `/api/v1/agent/agents?board_id={board_id}`
- Forbidden task route families: `/api/v1/agent/tasks`, `/api/v1/tasks`
- Canonical assignment marker: `ASSIGNMENT_AUTHORIZED: true`

